// useLlm.ts sendMessage: the done handler \(line 100-106\) calls unlisten after firing.
// So on first done: calls onComplete, then unlistenRef.current?.\(\) and sets it null.
// On second done: listener is already removed by first done handler. So onComplete NOT called twice.
// The self-unlisten on done means only the FIRST done event is processed. Safe.
console.log\('Self-unlisten on done: second done event is ignored. onComplete called exactly once.'\);
console.log\('But the TTS worker still receives the second None sentinel — it has already exited its loop.'\);
console.log\('Second send\(None\) returns Err \(channel closed\) and is silently discarded. Safe.'\);
")

