// useTts.ts ensureWorklet \(line 55-86\):
// The guard is: if \(workletReadyRef.current && workletNodeRef.current\) return;
// But if the AudioContext exists and addModule was already called, calling addModule again
// for the same module URL is a no-op per spec \(returns resolved promise\). Safe.
// However: if startStreaming is called concurrently \(two rapid user sends\), 
// ensureWorklet could run twice simultaneously before workletReadyRef is set to true.
// Both would call addModule and new AudioWorkletNode. Second node would be connected.
// Only the second node reference is stored \(workletNodeRef.current = node line 84\).
// The first node stays connected to destination but is orphaned \(no way to post to it\).
// This is a minor leak but not realistically triggerable in a mic-input app.
console.log\('Concurrent ensureWorklet: theoretical double-node leak, not practically triggerable'\);
")
